"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is passing a Pandas DataFrame with multiple columns directly to the heatmap function. According to the seaborn documentation, the data parameter of heatmap API should be a 2D dataset. If a Pandas DataFrame is provided, the index/column information will be used to label the columns and rows. However, in this case, the DataFrame 'tips' has multiple columns and the heatmap function will not know which column to use for the data. The correct usage would be to pivot the DataFrame to create a 2D dataset.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n---\\n> tips_pivot = tips.pivot_table(index='day', columns='sex', values='total_bill', aggfunc='mean')\\n> g = sns.heatmap(tips_pivot, square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\"\n}"